# Database (Prisma + Neon)

## Schema (`prisma/schema.prisma`)

| Model | Purpose |
|-------|---------|
| `User` | Auth; `role` + optional `makerId` |
| `Maker` | Workshop on map; pricing, status, printerTypes |
| `MakerFilament` | Material + color per maker (`printerType`, unique combo) |
| `Order` | Print job with dimensions, costs, delivery fields |

## Migrations

- Create: `npm run db:migrate` (loads `.env.local` automatically)
- Do not use `db:push` for production-like changes unless prototyping
- Custom SQL migrations live in `prisma/migrations/`

## Seed (`prisma/seed.ts`)

- 6 Prague makers with `MakerFilament` rows + 7 users
- Makers: `elena@workshop.cz`, `vinohrady@prints.cz`, etc.
- Run: `npm run db:seed`

## After schema changes

1. Edit `schema.prisma`
2. `npm run db:migrate`
3. Update `prisma/seed.ts` if seed data affected
4. Update `src/types/` and `map-*.ts` mappers
5. `npm run build` to verify types

## Filament options

Allowed materials/colors are validated in API against `src/lib/makers/filament-options.ts` (sourced from `capabilities.ts`). Keep DB values within these lists.
